body:
I've finished a first draft of the tutorial [here](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1etmwuGWziWTKM4a54f6EA7vm74wDRwulW7nX4KTtKK4). Please ignore everything after the **Advanced Table Configuration** header. That's the start of content to show users how to create custom formatting, metrics, dimensions, etc. that I'd like to add (let me know if you have any specific thoughts on items worth adding).

@mistercrunch let me know if you have any feedback, and please share with anyone who you think should review. I think it covers the lowest common denominator user, who's brand new to the concepts and language around Superset. 

If this looks OK, I can start mapping this to the docs in the actual source.

@alanmcruickshank very cool. My only feedback here would still be: is there a way to expose both the log data (potentially flattening some of the properties stored in the JSON, projecting them as easily-queryable values) and the slice / dashboard metadata in a more accessible way for querying, so that you enable admins to ask _any_ general questions of that data.

Again, I like the idea of your network viz for your use case, but I'm imaging admins asking _many_ arbitrary questions about their instance, and your viz might not target all of them.

Maybe this is a separate story from yours - just wanted to put the thoughts on paper in case they help.
